<h1>Documentation for API</h1>
<br />
<h4>Query Endpoints</h4>
<div>
  <table width="100%" border="1">
    <tr>
      <th>HTTP Method</th>
      <th>Endpoint API</th>
      <th>Authorization</th>
      <th>Description</th>
    </tr>

    <tr>
      <td>Post</td>
      <td>/users/auth/id</td>
      <td>Not required</td>
      <td>
        Enter searcher's email and search client data by client's ID. Returns
        data containing client ID, name, email and role.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Post</td>
      <td>/users/auth/name</td>
      <td>Not required</td>
      <td>
        Enter searcher's email and search client data by client's name. Returns
        data containing client ID, name, email and role.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Post</td>
      <td>/users/auth/username</td>
      <td>Required. Searcher must have admin role</td>
      <td>
        Enter searcher's email and search policies of client by client's name.
        Returns data containing policy ID, amount insured, email, inception
        date, installment payment and client ID.
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Post</td>
      <td>/users/auth/policy</td>
      <td>Required. Searcher must have admin role</td>
      <td>
        Enter searcher's email and search name of client by policy ID. Returns
        data containing policy ID, amount insured, email, inception date,
        installment payment and client ID.
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
</div>
<br />
